# Dual-Tool Workflow Rules

## Role Division

| Task | Use |
|------|-----|
| Inline edit, quick fix, rename | Cursor AI |
| Screenshot / error image analysis | Cursor AI |
| Shell commands, git, npm scripts | Claude Code (terminal) |
| Multi-file refactor, new modules | Claude Code |
| Prisma schema + db push | Claude Code (must run from `apps/api/`) |
| Error from terminal/log paste | Either — paste as text to Claude Code |

## Conflict Prevention

1. **Check Claude Code is idle** before making Cursor inline edits on the same file
2. **Never auto-format on save** in a file Claude Code is actively editing — wait for Claude to finish
3. **Git commit frequently** — after each logical unit of work, commit so neither tool loses context

## Shared Linting
Both tools must respect:
- ESLint config in `apps/web/` — runs automatically after Claude Code edits
- TypeScript strict in `apps/web/`, loose in `apps/api/`
- No `console.log` left in production code

## Error Workflow
1. Screenshot error → paste into Cursor AI for visual analysis
2. Copy error text → paste into Claude Code terminal for fix
3. Claude Code fixes → Cursor reviews the diff inline

## Files Owned by Claude Code (do not edit manually)
- `CLAUDE.md` — update via Claude Code when architecture changes
- `apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma` — always run `npx prisma generate` after changes
- `apps/api/prisma.config.js` — Prisma v7 config, fragile
- `.claude/settings.json` — Claude Code hooks
